There seems to be a lot of questions in Atlassian Answers about this exact issue.  It would be helpful to include a link within the Close Issue Permissions setting stating that the workflow must have the Close Permissions Condition or the Close Issue Permission will not be applied and anyone will be able to close an issue. 

Or make the Close Permissions Condition copied over when a user clicks the new workflow button.  The Close Permission Condition is not copied by default to a workflow and many users are not aware that their project issues can be closed by anyone.

Certain ERROR-type messages in the *incoming mail log* are using the JIRA default language instead of English. (if the default language is not English) 
This causes some inconsistency and makes it difficult to troubleshoot errors because *not all log output* are in that language. So far as per my observations, all the DEBUG and INFO messages, and certain ERROR messages were in English regardless of JIRA's default language.

Example: The following error is in Russian:
{noformat}
Похоже, что сообщение было оправлено JIRA. Обработчик почты JIRA сконфигурирован для пересылки этих сообщений для избежания почтовых зацикливаний.
{noformat}
In English, it should be:
{noformat}
Message appears to have been sent by JIRA. JIRA's mail handler is configured to forward these messages to avoid mail loops.
{noformat}

*Steps to Reproduce:*
# Install JIRA Non-English language pack, e.g. Russian.
# Set JIRA default language to Russian.
# Restart JIRA.
# Force JIRA to hit into this error:
{noformat}
Message appears to have been sent by JIRA. JIRA's mail handler is configured to forward these messages to avoid mail loops.
{noformat}
by putting a notification email (coming from the same JIRA server) into one of JIRA's incoming mail handler folders. Observe the log output is in russian.

